hich are no longer used in their original state and now provide the setting for new uses. As disparate as the structures in question themselves are the structural and technological demands they impose on the architect. Whether the subject is energy-conscious renovation or progressive conversion, these new language editions of In Detail: Building in Existing Fabric incorporate innovative examples from Italy, France, and Spain developed specially for these volumes. Introductory essays by noted experts deal with the subject in depth from the perspectives of historical preservation, economy, and building technology. From a structure’s surrounding environment to large-scale representations of details, all of the drawings are meticulously researched and presented with the customary high quality and with the competence and experience of the editorial staff at DETAIL.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn Spanish, Castilian.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aBuildingsxRemodeling for other usevCase studies. 0aBuildingsxRemodeling for other use. 0aBuildingsxRepair and reconstruction. 4aGebäudesanierung. 4aUmnutzung von Gebäuden. 7aARCHITECTURE / Buildings / Public, Commercial & Industrial.2bisacsh1 aBurkhardt, Berthold, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJessen, Johann, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMoewes, Günther, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchittich, Christian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchittich, Christian, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSchneider, Jochem, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Architecture, Design and Arts 2000 - 2014z9783110635690oZDB-23-GAA08iTitle is part of eBook package: